article.headline: Tennessee State 87, Samford 85 (OT)
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Reiley Ervin scored his only second basket of the game with 4.2 seconds left in overtime to give Tennessee State an 87-85 victory over Samford on Thursday night. Both teams shot very well from the floor in a game that featured 25 lead changes and nine ties. Tennessee State (13-16, 8-7 Ohio Valley Conference) shot 67.9 percent for the game while Samford (15-12, 10-6) shot 65.9 percent. Kareem Grant came off the bench and missed only one shot in 12 attempts on his way to 26 points. Wayne Arnold had 18 points for the Tigers, while Eric King had 13 and Bruce Price 11. Randall Gulina and J. Robert Merritt both had 17 points to lead the Bulldogs, with Jerry Smith chipping in 12 and Jon Mills 11. Gulina sent the game to overtime tied at 78 with a layup in the final minute of regulation. In the extra period, Tennessee State scored five straight points to lead 83-78 with 2:44 left, but Smith scored and was fouled, hitting his free throw to bring the Bulldogs within 83-81. Mills made two free throws to tie it at 83 with 1:30 left in overtime. Grant made a dunk for the Tigers and Gulina converted two free throws with 20 seconds left to tie it again before Ervin's jumper won it for Tennessee State. The Tigers could make the conference tournament this year after going 7-21 overall and 6-10 in the league last season.
